rgence between inline comments and summary: a finding appears in the summary without a matching inline comment, or vice versa. This is a coordination failure between two separate outputs. A unit test of just the summary generation wouldn't catch this—the outputs might be generated from different code paths that fall out of sync. Testing requires running both operations together and verifying the set of findings is identical. Mocking the GitHub API (Integration) is sufficient to capture both outgoing API calls and compare their payloads.","test_description":"Mock the GitHub API to record all outgoing comment requests (both inline and summary). Run the agent. Extract the set of findings from each inline comment and the summary comment. Verify that the findings sets are identical: every inline comment issue appears in the summary, and the summary contains no extra findings not covered by inline comments.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The complete review workflow (read diff, analyze, post inline comments, post summary) executes successfully on a real PR without errors or manual intervention","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure mode includes infrastructure-level issues that Integration testing with mocks cannot catch: GitHub API authentication errors, rate limiting, network failures, repository permission issues, or unexpected edge cases in real PR structure (merge commits, large diffs, binary files, etc.). The phrase 'real pull request' in the behavior signals System-level scope. Integration testing can verify the orchestration logic with mocks, but only System level (actual GitHub interaction) can catch failures that emerge from real API contracts, timing, or repository state.","test_description":"Create a test pull request on a real GitHub repository (or test GitHub instance). Invoke the agent end-to-end without any manual steps. Verify that the agent completes without errors, successfully posts at least one inline comment, and posts a summary comment. Check for proper error handling if the API returns transient errors. Verify no partial state (e.g., inline comments posted but summary missing).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.6,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.05}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13253,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13253},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fb44e8eb-248c-4425-908c-2372914d5498","uuid":"5e7028b0-23e1-48a0-8359-c5a4619af49c"}
